RACE.FOOTNOTES: MALALA dug in, prevailed. MAGISTERIAL drift out, veered in sharply. MIDNIGHT SECRET altered path late. TAKEMETOTHECANDYSHOP chased leaders. IMPRESSIVE BROOK no menace. RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 5000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $3,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAPPY HAPPY HAPPY rushed up to prompt the pace from the inside to the quarter pole and took over and pulled away in the stretch. SNICKEL TE tracked the leaders through the turn then moved out to three wide at the quarter pole and was a clearly second best. TALLANDLONG went to the front under a pressured pace to the quarter pole when she was collared and tired, but stayed on for the show. STARLIGHT TWIST trailed the field through the turn then moved out four to five wide in upper stretch but was empty and improved her position. FETCHING FURY saved ground to no avail.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Special Weight Purse 10700. FOR COLORADO BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIGPARTY NOWHISKEY tracked the leaders from three wide then was asked at the quarter pole and engaged the leader, matched strides to deep stretch and edged away for the win. GUTFIELD battled for the lead early with outside rival then shook loose nearing the half pole to take the lead to the top of the stretch then was headed again and dueled down the stretch while fighting gamely but couldn't fend off the challenge and proved second best. PUT PUT PUT broke well then was forwardly placed from four wide then fell back slightly going into the turn, made a rebid in mid turn and was along for the show. OLD FASHION TIME raced near the back in the early stages the moved up from five wide at the three eighths pole and kept on to improve is position. SILENCE'S NATION dueled for the lead early then pressed the pace to the top of the stretch and weakened. CAN DANZER trailed the field while saving ground through the turn but was not a threat. YOU'RE MY ROCK raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early then dropped back on the turn but was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 6800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF A RACE IN 2023(RACES WHERE ENTERED FOR $4000 OR LESS NOT CONSIDERED). Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAN EDITION tracked the leaders around the first turn then moved between horses at the five furlong marker to take the lead, edged away on the final turn and drew off in the stretch. THE GREATEST EAGLE saved ground down the backstretch then moved out to three wide on the final turn to make a late run and just got up for the place. JUST CALL ME KEN raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then moved up from two wide around the final turn but weakened in the stretch drive and couldn't hold the place. FORT KNOX was off the pace down the backstretch then moved up from three wide on the final turn and tired in the stretch, fell after wire and was vanned off. UNBROKEN SONG shared the command to the five furlong marker then pressed the pace to the three furlong marker and gave way. MORHAWK trailed the field to the top of the stretch but remained back. NORTHRNDANCRSGHOST shared the command to the five furlong marker then retreated.

MAIUS was off the pace to the turn then made a bid at the three furlong marker and engaged the leader at the top of the stretch and dueled to the wire but was outkicked and proved to be second best. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Rocky Mountain Futurity ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 7 330 Y Dirt CR: 68. Futurity Purse 83940. 2 YEAR OLDS THAT QUALIFIED FOR THE FINALS. Weight 124lbs. Runs: Sunday July 9 Trials: Monday June 26. Closes: June 19. Nominations contact RMQHA.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUST RUN BY broke in, dueled, prevailed. HOWLIN AT THE MOON drifted in, game 2nd. BIANCAS FLARE steady drive for 3rd. SHEZ OUR DIVA drifted in, game effort. A BEAUTIFUL FLARE broke out, dueled, outkicked. LIEBRITA veered in, bumped foe. STICKY LOU WHO foe crossed path. ATHENA MAXIMUS bumped by foe, veered in. WINE TIME lost path early, steadied late. SIX GOOD KICKS steadied late. STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS POSTED INTO THE RUNNING IN MID STRETCH, AFTER A REVIEW THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED ATHENA MAXIMUS FROM EIGHTH TO NINTH AND LIEBRITA FROM SIXTH TO TENTH FOR INTERFERNCE.
